# JA4proxy-testing — 18-B CVE allowlist
#
# Entries here are CVEs explicitly accepted for a bounded window. Each
# CVE below MUST be preceded by an `# expires: YYYY-MM-DD` comment.
# scripts/ci/check_image_scan.py fails if any entry is expired —
# forcing a decision to fix, re-justify with a new expiry, or remove.
#
# Severity response times (from PHASE_18 acceptance matrix):
#   CRITICAL → decision within 7 days, fix within 30
#   HIGH     → decision within 30 days, fix within 90
#
# Only CRITICAL is a hard merge gate today; HIGH is informational
# until chunk 18-B-2 tightens the gate. That's why the current
# entries are all CRITICAL.
#
# NOTE: this list is the UNION of CRITICAL findings observed across
# CI runs. Results flap day-to-day because (a) Trivy's advisory DB
# refreshes and (b) several images we scan use floating tags
# (:latest, :2-alpine, :7-alpine) that re-resolve to different
# digests over time. Listing every CVE we've seen in a 30-day
# window prevents the gate from turning into a red-green coin flip.
# All entries below share the 2026-05-17 expiry; when that date
# arrives, each gets re-justified individually or the image moves.

# --- redis:7-alpine (Go 1.18.2 stdlib in upstream base) --------------
# Both CVEs are html/template flaws. Redis itself is not a Go
# html/template user — the vulnerable package is embedded via tools
# we don't invoke — so deployment impact is very low. Mitigation:
# move to redis:7.4-alpine or redis:8-alpine once pin+digest churn
# is budgeted.
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2023-24538
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2023-24540

# --- caddy:2-alpine (smallstep/certificates, grpc-go) ----------------
# Caddy's cert handling and gRPC surface are not on our public path:
# HAProxy terminates TLS as passthrough and Caddy only serves the
# static honeypot after JA4proxy. Fixes require upstream caddy
# image refresh.
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2026-30836
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2026-33186

# --- prom/blackbox-exporter:latest (Go stdlib crypto/tls) ------------
# Blackbox probes known internal/external targets over HTTPS from
# the monitoring network. Exploit requires MITM position on the
# probe path, so exposure is bounded but non-zero. Awaiting
# upstream image refresh against a fixed Go.
# expires: 2026-05-17
CVE-2025-68121
